"North Austin Civic Association","street":"817 Mc Phaul St","city":"Austin","postal_code":"78758","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":null,"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Jordan DesHotels","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXibpNKPvK30uMx3DSaHALBEaFeOF4cnUc85s0QS7jOF7YMpxY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I witnessed one of Wilkins Electric’s drivers get aggressively cut off by a reckless, entitled driver who clearly had zero regard for anyone else on the road. The Wilkins driver had every opportunity to escalate the situation—but didn’t.\n\nNo brake-checking. No road rage. No stupid retaliation.\n\nInstead, the Wilkins Electric driver stayed calm, controlled, and professional while the other driver acted like a complete clown. That tells you everything you need to know about this company.\n\nAnyone can slap a logo on a truck. Not everyone trains their people to keep their composure when provoked. Wilkins Electric clearly does. That level of discipline and professionalism doesn’t happen by accident—it comes from solid leadership and standards.\n\nIf this is how their team behaves under stress in traffic, I have zero doubt they bring the same professionalism, restraint, and competence to their work. Wilkins Electric earned my respect on the road—and that says more than any ad ever could.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nina T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZS1fUPDJISQFZ6AFphOreIkVMsTfUc4Z-acwiMyOnYWq0AE5J=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was driving down Burnet and their company truck almost hit my vehicle twice. I was trying to merge out of the turn lane and his vehicle almost hit me. Honked on my horn to alert him he was about to cause an accident, and left it at that. Continued driving and when he was in the lane next to me, he swerved to scare/hit my car. I called to make a complaint and he proceeded to cuss at me.\n\nVery unprofessional and honestly a danger to the road!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily Hirsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4EQBvpYTi27j0aMz_laV7SXzKT2367ioq7x0qC5bM6Cfs9oM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I broke down on the side of the road with a flat tire, and a Wilkin’s employee—I believe his name was Johnny—pulled over, asked if I was alright, blocked traffic with his truck so I could get out of my car safely, and changed my tire for me with no questions asked.  I can’t even express how grateful I was!! Please take your business here!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert Nason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUYoTCkW8ivzws3Im9rEaJv39W-nfzFPbqApVnbXFOaRUZsT8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So happy with their service. Not only did they come out promptly when we lost power to our house, they solved the issue quickly and for a very reasonable price. Very strong recommendation for Wilkins electric!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Beth Willowers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIYCey22PdMgc7lKqehVeptAWuTFE6F-FLodQs21XzNt669g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Although I haven’t used their services, I can sure tell you whomever was driving the big truck with their sign on it was an aggressive and rude driver. Yesterday, around 4pm, 290 eastbound, that guy was zipping in and out of lanes. He cut me off and several others. Glad there wasn’t a wreck. All of that to just get to the next red light where we all waited together. Not the best representative or advertising of your company.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Braden H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXO_BcOt-KJWHRTmcMTMX7lyboYzrH8L0As0eWtdB3yKDN3K4L8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"An older gentleman exited this business and started harassing us for doing business across the street. We tried to explain the situation and they responded with expletives and harassment. This has apparently been a problem for a number of years. I would hate to see how actual customers are treated.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZJHZN4l8GHDVYwoHfHpjQTb18qmLW175Y_QpadgTZeGzlLhfRoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The owner of this company tried to run us off the road this morning because he didn't like my driving. Imagine working with an electrician who can road rage a family car, my four year old and eight year old were terrified because he pulled up to their side and rolled down his window to scream and yell at us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Orion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUzWEUwjGkv2Mq2cB6XYWw9ow3zNA1syNvsZ0YWt9CdF4wydPY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This company gets the job done. If you want fast, straight to the point electrical work then this is the company to choose. Their prices are also reasonable and the employees are well trained in customer service.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
