to do to be up to code, since there was some new things since house was built. He also did a full house inspection to make sure nothing else was affected. He even went out of his way to help put up some lights for me while he was there since that was part of the problem. This was my first time using them, recommended from a neighbor. I highly recommend this company and will continue to use them. Thank you Mr. Electric!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0i7tV2br49fHpkP-F4Kph_uovW40v23XpLy52zhc1dhMouxxqkqQwxeFrf2Sodlj2DjqFZh8vRTEfJvl_S6_hyNbc_VBox-8vb_0x0Nnsj__oHcMbsSw5rRXfqXKq739d-zXNA5g3DuECo=k-no"],"When":"2025-7-16"},{"Name":"Andrew Garland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRxx3xlK2MEPBVGcwsARvEUN3BJ7rkHC0KNmGm6d4gUMrUgak=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The tech was on site for about an hour to replace 5 smoke detectors. They charged us $910.00. Mr. Electric made our \"Do Not Use Again\" list of contractors due to unreasonable pricing.\n\n10/10/2025 update: Mr. Electric honored our request for a 50% refund after an escalation of the pricing issue. We were ultimately charged $455 for the installation. It's our hope the feedback we provided will create real change in the company's pricing policy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"david simpson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzNto6f4a_aelNx88eJduITFydlv7oaeBeAYvLa2ih_a9wgLY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best price I could get in the area to install 230 in garage for electric vehicle.  Jon did an exact job. Can’t thank him enough","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jair Acevedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKaIwEp98WiU0j98rDy2CNhU7CpoPyLbhObsms_CfO0t5C6Ok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very professional, kind and provide options and details to fixing the problem. He was fast and keeping me informed of what is going on. This was great and now my kitchen lights are working. Thanks Joe","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bill Ricks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6Dj9Qt9HaQfcShB-OouNH1PTFPAddjwhLiy84fK833Da28w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had Mr. Electric change out 2 electrical panels, 2 smoke detectors, 2 electrical sockets and 2 light switches. They added an additional socket for our tankless water heater. They also did a check in each room of the circuitry.  They also installed our Ring doorbell. Jon and Hunter were extremely courteous and knowledgeable. They explained everything completely and were very fast. They cleaned up completely upon finishing all the jobs.  We have used Mr. Electric before and will continue to use them if we need any electrical work in the future. Thank you Jon, Hunter and Mr. Electric.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angela Auwarter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQpsO_NgHZOxfB-WO0ffr4P-zykC4OsUczGGt1iKHIqnNBkA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I received a 2400 estimate and refused service. I tried another electrician who talked me through several possible solutions. I was able to fix the issue with a simple battery change and no charge for a 20 minute conversation. The services recommended for 2400 wouldn't have even fixed the issue. Single women beware and get second opinions if something seems off.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick Stephens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQODrTgtr4vskhFMvwc8O_tT1i7oVAfU0VtaGDib9gkfwZdpiw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sketchy company!\n\nWe asked to get a quote on hanging a chandelier from a tall vaulted ceiling.  Nothing else, as we have a neighbor electrician who does our small jobs.\n\nThe electrician who came out prodded at every little thing he could find, clearly looking for extra work to suggest.  I asked why he needed to see both the main and sub panels, told me it was “company policy for their safety”.  No, you wanted to see if anything was wrong so you could charge for more work.  I’ve never had a company demand that for a simple job, and the two companies I got other quotes from had no such “safety” requirement. How very unsafe of them!\n\nI had scheduled my electrician neighbor to come over an hour later to troubleshoot a ceiling fan, but of course the Mr. Electric tech was still there, \u003e60 minutes just to get a simple quote.  As soon as he saw my neighbor, he frantically “had to make a phone call” out of nowhere.  He returned and told me he had to leave immediately and that they would not be providing me a quote anymore.  What??? Apparently another contractor coming over for a separate job is the garlic to their vampire money sucking operation.\n\nI politely asked that his manager give me a call to better explain the situation.  He called me that afternoon and we discussed the situation and company policies, and the manager promised me he would get back to me with a quote.  He never did!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Janis Kawamura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLNO0wZGrQGXzGwKi3NHRBKcwckw_8YUZY4l-hrRvU3mI10g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"James and Hunter are the most trustworthy electricians ever!   They installed new electrical systems and did it professionally and precisely!  I am very happy with the results!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
